	<LEVEL style-name="Title" style-name-escaped="Title" style-id="0-0-0-474" level-depth="1" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-42408" number="50896" version="1245">
			<HEADING>Title 24: Department of Health and Mental Hygiene</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-15486" name="Title 24"/>Title 24: Department of Health and Mental Hygiene</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
			<RECORD id="0-0-0-42409" number="50897" version="3">
				<HEADING>Chapter 1: Required Signs</HEADING>
				<PARA>
					<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-5859" name="T24C001"/>Chapter 1: Required Signs</PARA>
			</RECORD>
			<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
				<RECORD id="0-0-0-42410" number="50898" version="92">
					<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-20">
						<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> Pursuant to City Record 1/15/2016, effective 2/14/2016, this chapter (formerly, &quot;Posting Regulations For Vendors of Alcoholic Beverages&quot;) was repealed and replaced in its entirety. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
					</PARA>
				</RECORD>
			</LEVEL>
			<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
							<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-42411" number="50899" version="3">
									<HEADING>§ 1-01 Vendors of alcoholic beverages.</HEADING>
									<PARA>
										<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-5861" name="T24C001_1-01"/>§ 1-01 Vendors of alcoholic beverages.</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42412" number="50900" version="1848">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Definitions. </CHARFORMAT>Words and terms used in this section have the same meaning as in § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="17-173" destination-id="0-0-0-0">17-173</LINK>(a) of the Administrative Code, except that terms not defined in such § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="17-173" destination-id="0-0-0-0">17-173</LINK>(a) have the same meaning as terms defined in the Alcoholic Beverage Control Law. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42413" number="50901" version="3">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Applicability.</CHARFORMAT> This section applies to owners, operators, and other persons in control of any business establishment that, pursuant to the Alcoholic Beverage Control Law, is required to obtain a license for the retail sale of alcoholic beverages for (i) consumption on the premises, or (ii) for consumption off the premises excluding grocery stores or supermarkets where the primary business purpose is the sale of foods, dry goods, household supplies, and beverages other than alcoholic beverages. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42414" number="50902" version="3">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Posting. </CHARFORMAT>Owners, operators and other persons described in subdivision (b) of this section must post in each applicable business establishment a sign, provided by the Department, in a conspicuous place visible to patrons, with the following text: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42415" number="50903" version="1122">
										<PARA>
											<PARAFORMAT justify="center">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">WARNING: Drinking alcoholic beverages during pregnancy can cause birth defects.</CHARFORMAT>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARAFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42416" number="50904" version="91">
										<PARA>(Added City Record 1/15/2016, eff. 2/14/2016) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
								</LEVEL>
							</LEVEL>
							<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-42417" number="50905" version="3">
									<HEADING>§ 1-02 Dangerous underwater breathing behaviors.</HEADING>
									<PARA>
										<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-5863" name="T24C001_1-02"/>§ 1-02 Dangerous underwater breathing behaviors.</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42418" number="50906" version="1127">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Definitions. </CHARFORMAT>Words and terms used in this section have the same meaning as in 24 RCNY Health Code <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24HC_165.00" destination-id="0-0-0-15031">Article 165</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42419" number="50907" version="1127">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Applicability. </CHARFORMAT>This section applies to persons owning or operating swimming pools who are required to have a permit issued by the Commissioner pursuant to 24 RCNY Health Code <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24HC_165.00" destination-id="0-0-0-15031">Article 165</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42420" number="50908" version="3">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Posting. </CHARFORMAT>Swimming pool permittees must post a sign, in a location easily seen from the pool deck of each pool in a bathing facility, and in each dressing area, warning swimmers of the dangers of taking deep breaths, one after the other, before swimming underwater, and the prohibition of breath-holding contests. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42421" number="50909" version="3">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Sign specifications. </CHARFORMAT>Signs must: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42422" number="50910" version="3">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Be constructed of durable, resilient, water resistant metal, plastic or other material acceptable to and approved by the Department; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42423" number="50911" version="3">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Measure at least 17&quot; in width and 22&quot; in height; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42424" number="50912" version="3">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Bear the pictorial design and text that appears in Appendix 1A of this Chapter that is either downloaded from the Department&apos;s website or otherwise obtained from the Department, and that when reproduced incorporates the language, color, size of type, imagery, and other specifications of the Department&apos;s pictorial design. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42425" number="50913" version="1122">
										<PARA>
											<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
											<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Penalties. </CHARFORMAT>Swimming pool permittees who are issued notices of violation returnable to the Hearings Division at the Office of Administrative Trials and Hearings must pay a penalty of $200 per violation sustained for (i) failure to post the sign, (ii) posting a sign without the Department&apos;s required pictorial design or text or as otherwise specified in <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24C001_App1a" destination-id="0-0-0-15267">Appendix 1A</LINK> of this Chapter and subdivision (d) of this section, or (iii) not posting a sign in a location that is easy to see from the pool deck of each pool in a bathing facility, and in each dressing area. If a person issued a notice of violation fails to appear and is found in default for a violation cited under this section, any penalties to be imposed for such sustained violation will be doubled. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-42426" number="50914" version="91">
										<PARA>(Added City Record 1/15/2016, eff. 2/14/2016) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-001]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
								</LEVEL>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
